Package: anatomogramdata
Title: Tidy Human Anatomogram Polygon Data from the EBI Expression Atlas Source
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Peter", "Tanksley", email = "peter_tanksley@txstate.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides tidy, ontology-tagged, ggplot2-ready human anatomogram
    polygon data (hgMale/hgFemale), parsed directly from the EBI Expression
    Atlas anatomogram SVG source (Apache-2.0 code / CC-BY-4.0 images) rather
    than relying on a frozen hardcoded snapshot. This is a data package, not
    a plotting package -- plot the bundled data with ggplot2::geom_map(),
    which already provides full aesthetic flexibility (see examples/).
    Inspired by and structurally indebted to the gganatogram package
    (Jesper Maag et al.), but built independently from the underlying
    source rather than as a fork of its code or bundled data.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/petertanksley/anatomogramdata
BugReports: https://github.com/petertanksley/anatomogramdata/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0.0)
